HEADWORD: Æthogen
<hw>⟦AE⟧th"o*gen</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>a'i`qw</grk> fire, light + <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A compound of nitrogen and boron, which, when
heated before the blowpipe, gives a brilliant phosphorescent; boric
nitride.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

